Package: optimaltrees
Type: Package
Title: Optimal Decision Trees with Flexible Loss Functions
Version: 0.4.0
Author: OptimalTrees Development Team
Maintainer: OptimalTrees Development Team <optimaltrees@example.com>
Description: Optimal decision tree learning with support for classification and
    regression. Implements branch-and-bound optimization to find provably optimal
    trees under various loss functions (misclassification, log-loss, squared error,
    absolute error, Huber, quantile) with support for custom user-defined losses.
    Includes Rashomon set enumeration for exploring multiple near-optimal trees.
    This package uses direct Rcpp bindings to the integrated C++ implementation,
    eliminating external dependencies for easier distribution and better performance.
License: MIT
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.0), jsonlite (>= 1.7.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: testthat, knitr, rmarkdown
SystemRequirements: C++11, GMP (GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
